          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-368-25OB-line-1" n="1">They write from Dublin, that when Dean Sw──t went to attend the Lord Lieutenant, after tarrying some Time in the Levee-Room, he wrote the following Distich on an old Card.</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-368-25OB-line-2" n="2">
              <hi rend="italics">My very Good Lord, 'tis a very hard Task,</hi>
            </l>
            <l xml:id="swift-368-25OB-line-3" n="3"><hi rend="italics"/><hi rend="italics">That I shou'd thus wait, who have nothing to ask</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-368-25OB-line-4" n="4">Which being handed to his Lordship; it was return'd with this Answer:</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-368-25OB-line-5" n="5">
              <hi rend="italics">My very good Dean, there are few who come here</hi>
            </l>
            <l xml:id="swift-368-25OB-line-6" n="6"><hi rend="italics"/><hi rend="italics">But have something to ask, or something to fear</hi>.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
